This paper deals with the interference channel in MIMO systems, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the use of channel state information (CSI) in the system, which falls under the sub-categories of network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses achievable schemes and DoF regions, which are topics in multiple access (cs.MM) and communication theory (cs.CE).
